**Idea:** I used 3-Way QuickSort Partitioning Technique which is as follows: we set a pivot, then we keep elements less than pivot on left side and greater than pivot on right side and elements equal to pivot will be in the middle. 
**For Example:** we have an array [2, 2, 0, 1, 0, 1], we set pivot to 1 then our array will be [0, 0, 1, 1, 2, 2]
**Implementation:** How can we implement that? 
1. Left pointer - so we will keep storing `element < pivot` from left side
2. Right pointer - so we will keep storing `element > pivot` from right side

setting left and right pointers
```
int l = 0, r = a.size() - 1;
```

We will go from `0 to r` ... and if we encounter any `element > pivot `  hence decrementing` r `will help us not to evaluate element that is already fixed to the right side
```
for(int i = 0; i <= r; i++)
```
1. If `element < pivot`, put current element on the left side, and increase `l`
2. if `element > pivot` put current element on the right side, and decrease `r` and also decrease `i` becasue the element which was on the right with which we swapped current element has to be checked. 
```
if(a[i] < p) {
	swap(a[i], a[l]);
	l++;
} else if(a[i] > p) {
	swap(a[i], a[r]);
	r--;
	i--;
}
```
