# Easy, Fast and Beginner Friendly ✅
# Intuition
We can solve this problem using Dutch Flag Algorithm.

    Runtime - 100%🔥 
    Memory - 91.13%🔥

# Approach
1. Firstly we will assume that all 0's are on the left of low pointer and all 2's are on right of high pointer.
2. Then we apply the above rule for nums array, we will check each element in nums array with the help of mid pointer :
3. If nums[mid] = 0 then we will swap it with nums[low](as all 0's should be on left of low) and will increase low and mid.
4. If nums[mid] = 1 then it is at its correct position so no need to swap we will just increase mid.
5. if nums[mid] = 2 then we will swap it with nums[high](as all 2's should be on right of high) and will decrease high.(But will not update mid as at mid there will be a new value which could be 0).


# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(N)
- Space complexity: O(1)

#  If you like the solution and understand it then Please Upvote.⬆️❤️ 
	* PEACE OUT LUV✌️*

