# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
There are two approaches :  
**APPROACH 1:**
1. Count the number of zeros, ones and twos as it is already gievn that array contains only these three elements.
2. First fill the zeros then ones and at last twos in the array.


**APPROACH 2:**
 This is a three pointer approach 
1. First pointer is pointing to the index where the next zero is going to be stored.
2. Second pointer is pointing to the index where the next one is going to be stored.
3. On encountering the zeros and ones swap these elements with the respected pointers which points to their exact positions.
# Complexity
- Time complexity:O(N)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:O(1)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

