solutions.content:
The Dutch National Flag Algorithm is a linear-time sorting algorithm for sorting elements that can be classified into three different categories. It is commonly used to sort arrays that consist of only 0s, 1s, and 2s.

Here are the steps for implementing the Dutch National Flag Algorithm:

1. Initialize three pointers, low, mid, and high, to the beginning, middle, and end of the array.
2. Set mid to low.
3. While mid is less than or equal to high:
    - If the element at mid is 0, swap it with the element at low and increment both low and mid.
    - If the element at mid is 1, increment only mid.
    - If the element at mid is 2, swap it with the element at high and decrement high.
4. The array is now sorted.

# Code
```
//Dutch National Flag Sort Algorithm
//for sorting problem with 3 unique values 
class Solution {
public:
    void sortColors(vector<int>& nums) {
        int low = 0 ; //1st mid value ; 
        //Before which everthing is low(Blue)
        int mid = 0 ; //1st Unknown Value :
        //low to mid is mid value about which we dont care to swap ;
        //mid to high all unknown values
        int high = nums.size()-1 ; //last Unknown Value
        //after mid all highs(Red) ;


        int blue = 0 ;
        int white = 1 ;
        int red = 2 ;

        while(mid <= high) { // as mid crossed high i.e 1st unknow val crossed last unknown val
        //i.e no more unknown value remains

            if (nums[mid] == blue) {//here
                swap(nums[mid] , nums[low]) ;
                low++ ; //as low ke peeche saare blue ;
                mid++ ;//val at mid was revealed somove it further to continue being 1st unknown
            }
            else if (nums[mid] == red) {
                swap(nums[mid] , nums[high]) ;
                high-- ; //as red ke right mai saar red
                //here mid wont be updated cause we have swapped it with unknown val at red
                //so mid  still 1st unknown ;
            }
            else if (nums[mid] == white) {
                //we dont care about white , no swap ;
                //but to maintain mid as the 1st unknown 
                mid++ ;
            }
        }

    }
};
```

