Easy walk through for making proper impression on the interviewer.
Firstly, talking about the **method 1 : Counting Sort Method**

-> In this method, we simply need to traverse the array and count number of occurrences of 0, 1 and 2.
-> Then, doing in-place operation by placing 0's upto count0, 1's upto count1 and 2's upto count2.

```
int c0=0, c1=0, c2=0;
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            if(nums[i] == 0)
                c0++;
            else if(nums[i] == 1)
                c1++;
            else
                c2++;
        }
        int i = 0;
        while(c0--)
            nums[i++] = 0;
        while(c1--)
            nums[i++] = 1;
        while(c2--)
            nums[i++] = 2;
```


