Java Solution with commented code and basic logic

**Logic:**
low and mid = 0 and high = nums.length 
mid == 0 ⇒ swap low and mid then mid++,low++
mid == 1 ⇒ mid++ mid == 2 =⇒ swap mid and high then high--

**Code**
```
 class  Solution {
    public  void  sortColors(int[] nums)
    {
     //step1: first declare the low,mid,high and temp for swapping later
      int  low = 0;
     int  mid = 0;
     int  high = nums.length-1;
     int  temp;
     //step2: use loop to iterate nums[] and switch case to see if value is 0 or 1 or 2
    while(mid<=high){ // because the loop wont swap if mid>high
        switch(nums[mid]){
          case  0: // now as mid == 0 swap mid with low and increment mid and low by 1
             temp = nums[low];
             nums[low] = nums[mid];
             nums[mid] = temp;
             low++;mid++;break;

         case  1:// now as mid == 1 we will just increment mid by 1
         mid++; break;

          case  2:// as mid == 2 swap mid with high and only decrement high by 1
           temp = nums[mid];
           nums[mid] = nums[high];
           nums[high] = temp;
          high--;
          break;
             } // end of switch
         } //end of while
     }
}
