Naive approach is to use linear search and go from 0 to length and check if element at current index >= length-currentIndex. If condition true return length-currentIndex.
If loop finishes return 0.
Better approach is to use binary search as we know data is sorted.
Apply classic binary search 
if arr[mid]==arr[length-mid] return length-mid. 
else if arr[mid]>arr[length-mid] set end=mid-1
else set start=mid+1;
once loop terminates we know start will be at correct position and since we wanted to return count. Answer will be length-start.

