We realize that h-index will be in range (0, n) inclusive. So we will binary with left=0 and right=n. Let mid = (left+right)/2. if mid is our h-index, it has to satisfy conditions: citations[n-mid]>=mid (exactly mid paper has at least mid citations) and citations[n-mid-1]<=mid (other n-mid paper has no more than mid citations each). Let res be the result.If citations[n-mid]<mid, then res < mid. If citations[n-mid-1]>mid, then res > mid. 
