# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Here's how the algorithm works:

Initialize left to 0 and right to the last index of the array.
Run a binary search to find the h-index.
In each iteration, calculate mid.
Check if citations[mid] is greater than or equal to n - mid. If it is, it means there are at least n - mid papers with at least n - mid citations.
If the condition is met, move right to mid - 1 to search for a smaller h-index.
If the condition is not met, move left to mid + 1 to search for a larger h-index.
Repeat the binary search until left is greater than right.
The h-index is equal to n - left after the binary search.
